{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 118738, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "server557", "body": "This NPC is referred to in the Warcraft book: of Blood and Honor. He referrers to some parts of this book when you are on the quest Eitrigg's Wisdom, such as mentioning he lived as a hermit near Hearthglen, and referring to an old friend, aka Tirion Fordring and his battle against him. More info located at http://www.wowwiki.com/Eitrigg", "date": "2007-07-10T19:18:33-05:00", "rating": 33, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Avoiding spoilers as best I can, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=1855]Tirion's[/url] dealings with Eitrigg were directly responsible for the events that led to him becoming an embittered exile in the Plaguelands.  ...Which may be a [i]good[/i]thing considering Arthas' subsequent [url=http://i151.photobucket.com/albums/s132/kadirsilvermace/Dialogue%20gags/Sith.jpg]betrayal of the paladins[/url].  EDIT: It appears that by the time of [i]Rise of the Horde[/i] which is narrated during Thrall's rule, Eitrigg has become one of his most trusted advisors.", "creationdate": "2008-07-22T11:32:16-05:00", "id": 40442, "rating": 18, "commentid": 118738, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TriniKrusader", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
