{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 1608323, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "andrtan", "body": "Some interesting lore facts about Eitrigg:\r\n1) Eitrigg lived alone in what is known now as [zone=139] starting from the the first war and up until the events of warcraft 3. Eitrigg abandoned the orcs because of his devotion to the old orcish tradition and honor and simply could not stand for what happened to his kind from the demonic corruption.\r\n\r\n2) Eventually he was discovered by [npc=38995] Fordring and after a skirmish with tirion both fighters were impressed with the extent of honor each showed in battle causing Eitrigg to save tirion's life from a collapsing tower saying: \"No honorable warrior deserves to die like a trapped animal\". Later on tirion repaid the favore by saving Eitrigg's life from being executed in Stratholme.\r\n\r\n3) At that time Eitrigg was recruited to the new horde by [npc=48051] when he was war chief to help thrall rebuild the horde and to teach them of the old ways, honor and virtue.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested to learn more, read \"Of blood and honor\" by Chris Metzen.", "date": "2012-01-07T18:47:09-06:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 2625435, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "pope3909", "body": "Eitrigg can be found at 57.7, 101.1 on the second level of the same ship as the Mission Command Table. He offers the ability to research new mission perks using War Resources.", "date": "2018-10-22T20:20:56-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 2575007, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "hevgirl", "body": "[b]- Research Options -\r\n[/b][small][i]These resemble Legion's Order Hall advancements as they provide a tree of options you can select to change your gameplay throughout BfA.[/i][/small]\r\n\r\nAlliance characters can research with [npc=132357] on [i]Wind's Redemption[/i] boat in Boralus.\r\nHorde characters with [npc=137472] on [i]The Banshee's Wail[/i] boat at the Zuldazar docks.\r\n\r\nall of these options use [currency=1560], which are also used to recruit troops and run missions.\r\n\r\n------ ---- -- ---- ------ ---- -- ---- ------\r\n\r\n[b]- Tier 1 -[/b]\r\nReq lvl 114\r\n[currency=1560] x15\r\n4hr research time\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=551][/li]\r\n[li]Harness the power of the sea, reducing the cooldown of your Hearthstone by 50% when used in Kul Tiras and Zandalar.[/li]\r\n[/ul][ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=552] A. / [order-advancement=548] H.[/li]\r\n[li]Capture the momentum from your recent flight path, increasing your mounted movement speed by 20% for 5 minutes upon landing.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n------ ---- -- ---- ------ ---- -- ---- ------\r\n\r\n[b]- Tier 2 -[/b]\r\nReq lvl 118\r\n3+ War Champions\r\n[currency=1560] x100\r\n1 day research time\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=549][/li]\r\n[li]Construct a larger barracks for your army, increasing the maximum number of troops you can house by 2.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=554] A. / [order-advancement=550] H.[/li]\r\n[li]Open a portal for transportation of troops from SWind/Org, allowing troops to be recruited instantly.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n------ ---- -- ---- ------ ---- -- ---- ------\r\n\r\n[b]- Tier 3 -[/b]\r\nReq lvl 120\r\n10 Island Expeditions Completed\r\n[currency=1560] x150\r\n1 day research time\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=655][/li]\r\n[li]Learn the pirate secrets of spotting treasure, increasing the amount of Seafearer's Doubloons you find on Island Expeditions by 20%.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=656][/li]\r\n[li]Learns the secrets of ancient civilizations. Increasing the duration of effects from shrines by 20%.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n------ ---- -- ---- ------ ---- -- ---- ------\r\n\r\n[b]- Tier 4 -[/b]\r\nReq lvl 120\r\n5+ War Champions\r\n[currency=1560] x200\r\n1 day research time\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=657][/li]\r\n[li]Construct an Azerite detector on your ship, granting you a chance to find additional Azerite when completing World Quests.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=658][/li]\r\n[li]Upgrade your Flight Master's Whistle, allowing you to call for a quick flight back to Zuldazar/Boralus when using your whistle directly next to a flight master on Zandalar or Kul Tiras.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n------ ---- -- ---- ------ ---- -- ---- ------\r\n\r\n[b]- Tier 5 -[/b]\r\nReq lvl 120\r\nWarfront victory against 3 unique enemy Commanders\r\n[currency=1560] x250\r\n1 day research time\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=659][/li]\r\n[li]Learn more efficient ways to gather resources under pressure, increasing resource gathering speed by 15% while fighting in a Warfront.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=667] A. / [order-advancement=660] H.[/li]\r\n[li]Learn how to best inspire allies in combat, increasing the effectiveness of nearby troops by 15% while fighting in a Warfront.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n------ ---- -- ---- ------ ---- -- ---- ------\r\n\r\n[b]- Tier 6 -[/b]\r\nReq lvl 120\r\nRevered with 3 Kul Tiras/Zandalar reputations: [achievement=12947]\r\n[currency=1560] x500\r\n1 day research time\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][order-advancement=668] A. / [order-advancement=661] H.[/li]\r\n[li]Open up additional lines of trade with your new allies, granting additional War Resources from emissary quests.[/li]\r\n[/ul]", "date": "2018-06-20T01:23:52-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1285714, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "760118", "body": "where is this guy located? I can't find him", "date": "2011-01-09T11:30:31-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "His first phase is at Chiselgrip. He will phase in at Flame Crest after you first complete all Flamestar Post quests and then complete most of the Chiselgrip quests. The Flamestar Post quests end with [quest=28426]. Chiselgrip's [quest=28439] does not need to be completed, but needs to be accepted and followed. While following you need to complete the auto-accept [quest=28441], which ends with an escort of Eitrigg (and Ariok) to Flame Crest (in [quest=28442]). After completing that last escort quest, I relogged and saw Eitrigg, offering [quest=28445], [quest=28443], and [quest=28444].", "creationdate": "2013-07-18T01:17:36-05:00", "id": 678339, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1285714, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "HotRats", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I gained about 1.5 levels of XP in my effort to get Eitrigg to Flame Crest. Wowwiki.com documents the complete quest progression, but it is unfortunately Alliance-centric.", "creationdate": "2013-07-18T09:55:49-05:00", "id": 678405, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1285714, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "HotRats", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
